The paper discusses probabilistic constructions of computable objects, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The Lov\'asz local lemma is a fundamental tool in probabilistic combinatorics, which is a subfield of discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the paper may also belong to information theory (cs.IT), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and probability (cs.PR).
